The paper discusses Neural Architecture Search (NAS) and proposes a new framework called Bayesian Meta Architecture SEarch (BASE) for efficient and scalable architecture search across multiple tasks. This involves learning a task-agnostic representation that can be used to speed up the process of architecture search. Given that the paper focuses on machine learning and deep learning techniques, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper specifically applies the proposed framework to the task of image classification, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also a likely sub-category. Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CL (Computation and Language) as they are all relevant to the topic of architecture search and machine learning.
